{
  "video_id": "V8miLevRI_o",
  "title": "Vermicomposting: How worms can reduce our waste - Matthew Ross",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13810.0,
      "end_time": 17453.0,
      "text": "Think of all the food made in the world each year."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17453.0,
      "end_time": 18701.0,
      "text": "Hard to picture?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18701.0,
      "end_time": 21427.0,
      "text": "Then, imagine that you are all of humanity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21427.0,
      "end_time": 22693.0,
      "text": "and on a plate in front of you"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22693.0,
      "end_time": 26423.0,
      "text": "is the one lovely annual meal you make for yourself."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26423.0,
      "end_time": 29139.0,
      "text": "You did all sorts of work putting that meal on your table."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29139.0,
      "end_time": 31860.0,
      "text": "You must be eager to consume the fruits of your labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31860.0,
      "end_time": 35707.0,
      "text": "And the vegetables.and meats and waffles of your labor, too, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35430.0,
      "end_time": 39997.0,
      "text": "Well, oddly enough, a third of that meal ends up in the trash."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39680.0,
      "end_time": 42535.0,
      "text": "A third of the food we eat globally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42535.0,
      "end_time": 49095.0,
      "text": "an estimated 1.3 billion tons ends up as waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 49382.0,
      "end_time": 52377.0,
      "text": "All the work we put into producing that food is wasted."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 52377.0,
      "end_time": 54797.0,
      "text": "And what's worse, it costs us."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 54797.0,
      "end_time": 59659.0,
      "text": "America alone spends an estimated165 billion dollars a year"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 61401.0,
      "end_time": 62279.0,
      "text": "We're wasting food, energy and and money."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 65420.0,
      "end_time": 67461.0,
      "text": "we're wasting the chance to change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 67461.0,
      "end_time": 70764.0,
      "text": "to make the system of food consumption more efficient."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 70764.0,
      "end_time": 72311.0,
      "text": "If you want to bring on that change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 72311.0,
      "end_time": 78058.0,
      "text": "you should know about a humble yet diligent and ever-so-crucial ally: the worm."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 78147.0,
      "end_time": 79814.0,
      "text": "Worms convert organic waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 79814.0,
      "end_time": 83358.0,
      "text": "and other compostable products into natural fertilizers."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 83358.0,
      "end_time": 86094.0,
      "text": "Up to 75% of what we put in the waste stream"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 86094.0,
      "end_time": 88512.0,
      "text": "can become food and bedding material"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 88512.0,
      "end_time": 90337.0,
      "text": "for vermicomposting."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 90337.0,
      "end_time": 92493.0,
      "text": "You can create a worm bin in your own home"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92493.0,
      "end_time": 95221.0,
      "text": "to see the composting process in action."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 95221.0,
      "end_time": 96714.0,
      "text": "First off, you need worms"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96714.0,
      "end_time": 98499.0,
      "text": "and not your typical earthworms."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 98499.0,
      "end_time": 99792.0,
      "text": "You need redworms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99792.0,
      "end_time": 101650.0,
      "text": "eisenia foetida,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 101650.0,
      "end_time": 103140.0,
      "text": "the species responsible for most"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103140.0,
      "end_time": 105389.0,
      "text": "vermicomposting in North America."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 105389.0,
      "end_time": 107671.0,
      "text": "These red wigglers are surface dwellers"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 107671.0,
      "end_time": 109058.0,
      "text": "who don't burrow too deep,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 109058.0,
      "end_time": 111601.0,
      "text": "they're optimal feeders around room temperature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111601.0,
      "end_time": 114270.0,
      "text": "and they're well-suited to converting organic waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 114270.0,
      "end_time": 116022.0,
      "text": "into usable fertilizer"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 116022.0,
      "end_time": 118149.0,
      "text": "Now, your worms might be vermin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 118149.0,
      "end_time": 120610.0,
      "text": "but they need a comfortable space to live and work:"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 120610.0,
      "end_time": 121673.0,
      "text": "some bedding materials,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 121673.0,
      "end_time": 123285.0,
      "text": "either shredded paper or cardboard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 123285.0,
      "end_time": 124343.0,
      "text": "some moisture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 124343.0,
      "end_time": 126103.0,
      "text": "and, of course, food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 126103.0,
      "end_time": 127950.0,
      "text": "namely, your leftovers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 127950.0,
      "end_time": 130452.0,
      "text": "slightly decomposed table scraps."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 130452.0,
      "end_time": 132121.0,
      "text": "The worms break down food waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 132121.0,
      "end_time": 134509.0,
      "text": "and other organic matter into castings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 134509.0,
      "end_time": 136959.0,
      "text": "a fancy synonym for worm poop."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 136959.0,
      "end_time": 140046.0,
      "text": "Their excrement is absolutely teeming with microbes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 140046.0,
      "end_time": 142087.0,
      "text": "which continue the decomposition process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 142087.0,
      "end_time": 144505.0,
      "text": "making all those once-wasted nutrients"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 144505.0,
      "end_time": 146892.0,
      "text": "available again as fertilizer."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 146892.0,
      "end_time": 148978.0,
      "text": "The timeline for the whole process varies"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 148978.0,
      "end_time": 150564.0,
      "text": "depending on the quantity of worms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 150564.0,
      "end_time": 151481.0,
      "text": "the temperature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 151481.0,
      "end_time": 154110.0,
      "text": "and how much waste is added to the bin."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 154110.0,
      "end_time": 156104.0,
      "text": "And there's another timeline to consider."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 156104.0,
      "end_time": 157897.0,
      "text": "In a healthy worm-bin habitat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 157897.0,
      "end_time": 159887.0,
      "text": "worm reproduction will occur"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 159887.0,
      "end_time": 162178.0,
      "text": "when the wigglers become sexually mature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 162178.0,
      "end_time": 166054.0,
      "text": "indicated by an elongation of the segments into a bulbous structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 166072.0,
      "end_time": 167907.0,
      "text": "Three-month old wigglers can produce"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 167907.0,
      "end_time": 172001.0,
      "text": "two to three semi-translucent yellow worm cocoons a week."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 172001.0,
      "end_time": 173789.0,
      "text": "You thought only moths and butterflies"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 173789.0,
      "end_time": 175081.0,
      "text": "come out of cocoons?"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 175081.0,
      "end_time": 177257.0,
      "text": "Well, we can't all be majestic."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 177257.0,
      "end_time": 180357.0,
      "text": "It takes around 11 weeks for new babies to hatch."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 180357.0,
      "end_time": 187739.0,
      "text": "When your bin seems to be full of living vermicelli noodles, it's time to share the bounty with your friends and start a vermicompost club."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 187797.0,
      "end_time": 189553.0,
      "text": "Or keep those worms to yourself"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 189553.0,
      "end_time": 191189.0,
      "text": "and start a business."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 191189.0,
      "end_time": 192807.0,
      "text": "Vermicomposting isn't confined"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 192807.0,
      "end_time": 194706.0,
      "text": "only to small worm bins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 194706.0,
      "end_time": 197532.0,
      "text": "it's an emerging entrepreneurial enterprise."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 197532.0,
      "end_time": 198813.0,
      "text": "Large-scale facilities convert"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 198813.0,
      "end_time": 201281.0,
      "text": "bulk organic waste and even manure"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 201281.0,
      "end_time": 204539.0,
      "text": "into rich, black castings called black gold."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 204539.0,
      "end_time": 207352.0,
      "text": "Its value as a soil additive is unparalleled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 207352.0,
      "end_time": 210434.0,
      "text": "and it can help plants resist harmful pathogens."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 210434.0,
      "end_time": 212774.0,
      "text": "The lack of available land in urban environments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 212774.0,
      "end_time": 215735.0,
      "text": "coupled with growing interest in smaller-scale farming"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 215735.0,
      "end_time": 218327.0,
      "text": "means there is a market for vermicomposting."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 218327.0,
      "end_time": 222154.0,
      "text": "Many communities use composting as part of zero-waste strategies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 222117.0,
      "end_time": 226819.0,
      "text": "and they can sell their worm-eaten table scraps to local farms, hungry for rich fertilizer."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 226878.0,
      "end_time": 228432.0,
      "text": "So, instead of wasting money,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 228432.0,
      "end_time": 230584.0,
      "text": "dumping wasted food in landfills,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 230584.0,
      "end_time": 232883.0,
      "text": "we can remake waste into an asset,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 232883.0,
      "end_time": 236412.0,
      "text": "putting it back into our food system to make it more sustainable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 236339.0,
      "end_time": 238201.0,
      "text": "all with the help of the humble worm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 238201.0,
      "end_time": 239885.0,
      "text": "the tiny organism that can help us"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 239885.0,
      "end_time": 242652.0,
      "text": "change the way we look at food's place in our lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 242652.0,
      "end_time": 244565.0,
      "text": "and our place in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 244565.0,
      "end_time": 245980.0,
      "text": "as long as we give the little guy"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 245980.0,
      "end_time": 247399.0,
      "text": "a place at our table."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 247399.0,
      "end_time": 249630.0,
      "text": "Well, not an actual seat at the table."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 249630.0,
      "end_time": 259630.0,
      "text": "A bin in the shed is fine."
    }
  ]
}